In MATLAB, you can compute the logarithm to the base 2 of a given number using the `log2` function. For the number 9, you can use the following code:

```matlab
number = 9;
log_base_2 = log2(number);
disp(log_base_2);
```

This will calculate the base-2 logarithm of 9 and display the result. If you prefer to use the natural logarithm and convert it to base 2, you can do it like this:

```matlab
number = 9;
log_base_2 = log(number) / log(2);
disp(log_base_2);
```

Both methods will give you the result for \( \log_2(9) \).
